&gt; Tucson opens the passenger&#39;s side door for Perceptor, hearing that he was 
&gt; on that side.  He was happy to have passengers, because to him, having his 
&gt; comrades around was a great comfort.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;Of course Perceptor, hop in, my door is open on the passenger side.  I 
&gt; just wish I could take all of you somewhere where we&#39;ve all never been 
&gt; before, but without my visual sensors, I&#39;m afraid my journeys are a bit 
&gt; restricted to sonar range.  I promise all of you though, that as soon as I 
&gt; am repaired, I would like to explore this planet with all of you, after we 
&gt; settle this crisis we&#39;re undergoing now.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; He had forgotten to talk to Perceptor not only as a leader, but as a 
&gt; friend.  This was a great opportunity to do just that.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; Perceptor, I&#39;ve been meaning to tell you something for a while, and I&#39;m 
&gt; sorry it wasn&#39;t right away.  But we have some time now, and I want you to 
&gt; know that I don&#39;t want you to feel enslaved under my command, I want you 
&gt; to know that you can always talk to me as a friend, and formality isn&#39;t a 
&gt; must around me.  All I ask is that you do your best, and if you don&#39;t 
&gt; succeed at something, do not hold that against you.  Everyone comes to a 
&gt; road block sooner or later, but those road blocks end up being learning 
&gt; experiences and when you come to it again, you learn how to get around it. 
&gt; That&#39;s how I want you and everyone else to feel.  Of course, the only 
&gt; thing that will bother me, is malice among comrades.  Other than that, I 
&gt; am by no means the punnishing type.  And if I&#39;ve forgotten to say this, 
&gt; I&#39;m saying it now.  Welcome to my aliance.  Your skills are most valuable 
&gt; to our factions, and I&#39;m honored to have you among us.&quot;
